What is an IP address and what is the difference between IPv4 and IPv6?  
Internet Protocol (IP) addresses are the unique numbers assigned to every computer or device that is connected
to the Internet. IPv4 internet addresses account for 4.3 billion devices in the world which is the total amount IPv4 provides However, IPv6 will provide much bigger space or up to 7 billion devices.

What is ICANN and how do they contribute to the global internet?
The Internet Corporation for Assigned Names and Numbers (ICANN) is an internationally organized, non-profit corporation that has responsibility for Internet Protocol (IP) address space allocation, protocol identifier assignment, generic (gTLD) and country code (ccTLD) Top-Level Domain name system management

TCP/IP:
What is the responsibility of TCP/IP?  a network protocol that defines the details of how data is sent and received through network adapters, hubs, switches, routers and other network communications hardware. 

Why are layers important to changing technology? Having layers keeps you from having to change the entire program to make changes
What types of applications run on the "application" layer? SMTP,FTP,HTTP,POP3,IMAP4,SNMP

Internet Security:
What is HTTP and how does it support the client-server model? Hyper Text Transfer Protocol is protocol that is used to type on the internet. requests are initiated by the recipient, usually the Web browser.Explain the protocols that secure HTTP uses to protect data

Explain the protocols that secure HTTP uses to protect data. It uses TLS protocol to encrypt communications.
 
